Transaction data streams through Kafka

Real-time feature engineering pipeline

Features fetched from Feast feature store

Multiple models score transaction in parallel

Ensemble decision with business rules

Results cached, alerts generated, feedback loop

Folder Structure:

fraud-detect-ml/
├── data/
│   ├── raw/           # Raw datasets
│   ├── processed/     # Processed features
│   └── external/      # External data sources
├── src/
│   ├── data/          # Data processing modules
│   ├── features/      # Feature engineering
│   ├── models/        # Model definitions & training
│   ├── serving/       # Model serving API
│   ├── monitoring/    # Model monitoring
│   └── utils/         # Utilities
├── notebooks/         # Exploratory analysis
├── tests/            # Unit & integration tests
├── deployment/       # Docker, k8s configs
└── pipelines/        # Training & batch pipelines

Core Features

Real-time Inference (<50ms latency)

Model Ensemble (XGBoost, LightGBM, Neural Network)

Feature Store (Feast for consistency)

A/B Testing framework for model deployment

Concept Drift Detection

Explainable AI (SHAP, LIME)

Feedback Loop for continuous learning

Performance Monitoring dashboard
